<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="2.[170,795,1882,2131]" lastBlockId="2.[869,1493,218,307]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[170,293,1882,1907]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Type data:</emphasis>
This species was described based on a single female collected by Otto Garlepp in 
<collectingRegion box="[574,685,1914,1939]" country="Peru" name="Apurimac" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Apurímac</collectingRegion>
, southern 
<collectingCountry box="[171,224,1946,1971]" name="Peru" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Peru</collectingCountry>
. Garlepp (1864‑1959) was a German naturalist and, as well as his brother Gustav (1862‑1907), a professional collector that worked actively in South America. The 
<typeStatus box="[170,271,2042,2067]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">holotype</typeStatus>
is currently housed at 
<collectionCode box="[533,597,2042,2067]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/5xp9-edpx" name="Universidade Federal do Parana, Colecao de Entomologia Pe. Jesus Santiago Moure" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="University or college">DZUP</collectionCode>
but according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S." box="[170,320,2074,2099]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" refId="ref4466" refString="Moure, J. S. 1999 [2000]. Algumas especies de Centris (Paracentris) (Hymenoptera, Anthophoridae). Acta BiolOgica Paranaense, 28 (1,2,3,4): 147 - 158. DOI" type="book" year="1999">Moure (1999)</bibRefCitation>
it belongs to the 
<collectionCode box="[521,584,2074,2099]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/9yp6-zxp9" name="Sao Paulo, Museu de Zoologia da Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="Museum">MZSP</collectionCode>
. The specimen has the following data label: 
<collectingRegion box="[457,565,2106,2131]" country="Peru" name="Apurimac" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Apurimac</collectingRegion>
<collectingCountry box="[574,624,2106,2131]" name="Peru" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Peru</collectingCountry>
[handwritten]\ [black‑rimmed] 
<taxonomicName authority="Schrottky" authorityName="Schrottky" authorityYear="1913" box="[1048,1344,218,243]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Hemisia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="garleppi">
<emphasis box="[1048,1230,218,243]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Hemisia garleppi</emphasis>
Schrottky
</taxonomicName>
<specimenCount box="[1353,1368,218,241]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
[handwritten] C.S. Schrottky det. 19 [printed] 12 [handwritten]\ recebido de J.F. Zikán Pe Moure 1942 [handwritten].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[869,1494,346,499]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[869,1004,346,371]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Comments:</emphasis>
This is a poorly known species recorded only in 
<collectingCountry box="[952,1005,378,403]" name="Peru" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Peru</collectingCountry>
. Considering the dark metasoma with terga 4 to 6 reddish brown, this species is probably related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Friese, 1899" authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1899" box="[871,1117,442,467]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caelebs">
<emphasis box="[871,977,442,467]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">C. caelebs</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Friese, H." box="[984,1117,442,467]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="39 - 48" refId="ref4037" refString="Friese, H. 1899. Neue arten der Bienengattungen Epicharis Klug und Centris Fabr. Termeszetrajzi Fuzetek, 23: 39 - 48." type="journal article" year="1899">Friese, 1899</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
which also has the same pattern of coloration.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
